	<http://www.cidoc-crm.org/cidoc-crm/P78_is_identified_by> "10th / 16th century (d. 1595)Prominent Šāfiʿī jurist. He was favourably disposed toward the Ṣūfīs. He was on familiar terms with the famous Egyptian Ṣūfī ʿAbd al-Wahhāb al-Šaʿrānī (d. 973/1565). Al-Ramlī's son-in-law Abū al-Mawāhib (d. 1037/1628) was a son of the Ṣūfī leader and poet Muḥammad al-Bakrī (d. 994/1586)\n               " .
